msContents.summary: Fragment of an Abbasid Qur'ān probably written in the third or fourth century H. / ninth or tenth century C.E, containing verses 27-52 from Sura al-Ibrāhīm (سورة ابراهيم); verses 9-99 fom Sura al-Ḥijr (سورة الحجر); verses 1-61 and 96-128 from Sura al-Naḥl (سورة النحل); verses 1-4, 37-63, and 68-107 from Sura al-Isrāʾ (سورة الإسراء); and verses 1-27 and 30-74 from Sura al-Kahf (سورة الكهف)

msItem.title: al-Qurʼān
القرآن
Qurʼān xiv:27-52; xv:9-xvi:61; xvi:96-xvii:4; xvii:37-63; xvii:68-xviii27; xviii:30-74
Sura al-Naḥl: One-hundred and twenty-eight verses (سورة النحل مائة وعشرون وثمان ايات)
Sura Subḥān (i.e. al-Isrāʾ): One-hundred and ten verses (سبحان مائة وعشر ايات) [line 3]

handNote.p: The script seems to correspond to the Abbasid Style NS I as described by François Deroche.

origin.origDate: 10th or 11th century AD /4th or 5th century Hijri
